	   <tr><td colspan=2>Twinking (people use a high level character to earn money then transfer it to another of their characters. This is done either by trusting a friend to hold onto it whilst you log onto your lower lvl char or simply putting both characters in the same quiet spot, and having the high level drop it, log off, log on as low lvl and pick it up). You're missing nothing at all.<br>You cannot earn 6k in Crushbone at lvl 16 BTW. You start to see the real money coming in at 40ish when you win the rolls for good items in groups. recently my wiz 41 has picked up Gaunts of The Black - 3k, Various Ry`Gorr armour pieces 2k total, and an Executioner's axe - 600pp. Although i do not money twink my SK16, I do item twink him alot - he is wearing the Gaunts and the Ry`Gorr pieces, as well as using a Drakkel Forged SledgeHammer that the wizzy bought for him. That is how it's done. Bit of a cheat - but hey.<br>Also I recommend wizzies or druids as great twinking classes because you need only put the recipient character on any wizzy spire and the job is done - wizzy just ports in and drops the stuff.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
