	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well I'm currently a 28 wizard (almost 29!  Portal spells!) and I still use the root and nuke method of soloing.  Until you get bonds of force and maybe after it's the only way to go.  One thing I have noticed is that against undead mobs and dark elves (inkies in mistmoore most specifically) the root tends to get resisted or wear off within 10 seconds almost constantly whether you DD nuke or not.  For this reason I've chosen to mostly solo in Lake of Ill Omen in kunark, where the sarnaks seem to love just standing there and getting blown apart.  Wizards past 24 have a serious mana problem, in that in order to gain experience you need to fight creatures with 500+ hp and that requires a lot of mana to nuke that much till later on.  with 900-1000 mana by level 30 you spend most of your time medding.  Either join a group with a chanter, or spend the majority of your time medding and/or begging for a clarity.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
