	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well everything you just read is great and tried and true. There are a few more risky ways of going about this.  In my wizy days 44lvl I actually try to get agro about half the time. I like to this short field kiting. When the pull shows up and everyone starts whacking and bombing away I tend to Blast a big one right off the bat.  Why you ask well in the true form of a wizy I always have my dmg sheild up. I will take 230-400 hp in dmg with my sheild why it tries to chase me or actually does hit me and that saves the heals for tanks and such.<br>Don't get me wrong the people I group with know what I'm doing otherwise they would think I'm crazy. Which might be the case but most of the time we don't have a true healer so this tactic sorta works like the snare fear without the fear, or I would be the one afraid and just running around. I first picked this up when grouping with a couple monks, they can't taunt to well so I decided oh well they are going to hit the mob no matter what and I just need to stay out of the way. Just a reminder people wizards have the largest range in how far away from a mob we can cast use this. There are many ways to not be on the mobs agro list atop the rest. this definately isn't one of them! I am merely pointing out that look we are wizards we tend to piss off everything we attack more than anything else, so go in there do the dmg you want to and run circles around your camp. If your lucky someone might notice that fact that they don't need healed after the fight and just keep pulling. BTW having sow, and snaring the mob is probably a bit inportant in this tactic.  I know I'm probably going to get a wrath of crap from a bunch of wizys for posting this, but if you think about every wizard has had to run for his life a bit when agroed, I'm just giving you an idea where your not scared typing posts like get him off me, or help or yelling. This is where I stand being a wizard we can pretty much kill single handedly (w/ full mana) what the group is going after. In the back of the mobs mind they know this and feel it when that nuke hits em.  So keep blasting and just keep out of the way. So next time your running for your life just think that your group is doing dmg while your moving out the way and your saving them the dmg. I know this sounds realy strange and people might not like this idea, but some of the places I have been recently we don't a tank with enough hp's or a healer that can keep them healed fast enough to stand toe to toe with the mobs. Have to imprevise somehow and being a risky wizy isn't so bad a proffesion, people tend to remember at the end of the night that, that wizy has some balls and was just as deep in the fight as the tank.    Well I will leave you all with that.  Viskius Katastrophy 44 Xeg<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
