<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9820145588061></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9820145588061><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=9820145588061>RE: Grouping Tactics</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=9820145588061#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Feb 12th 4:49 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Know your puller is probably the best thing in determining how to space your nukes.<br><br>If he's a good taunter to build aggro quickly you can start when the mob's down only 3/4 health or marginally before.  If the puller/taunter is not so fast at building aggro, then wait until 2/3 health of the  mob.   Throw one nuke, then med and throw a second when about 1/3 health.  Watch your party member's hit points...sometimes it's not bad to aggro the thing on you if your puller's about to die and the healer seems to be taking a nap.  you have to be in a group you trust for that though....<br><br>This has worked for me, as a general rule to follow.   BUT you'll have to adjust your nuking/stunning/rooting strategies to compliment the abilities of your group, and each group is different in it's own way.  <br><br>Live Learn and teach 'em who's Boss!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
