	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jan 25th 7:05 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm currently a 10th level Wizard hunting Giant Spiders in the West Commons. They are Yellow to me, but I've discoverd that by getting just within range of my fire bolt spell I can usually get two to three shots off before the spider gets to me. By the time he reaches me his health is down to about 25% so I let him hit me once (so the hit won't ruin my concentration) then immediatly follow with shock of frost. He usually runs at this time so I finnish him off with melee attacks to conserve manna. If he dosn't run at this point use shock of fire once or twice he'll get someware at this point. I usually have enough to get a second one before I have to med again. <br><br>One word of warning though; make sure there are no other monster around heading close to your location especially the Young Kodiaks.<br><br>This tactic rely's on the element of suprise and if done right gains good exp's. It got me through 9th and I'm about to level to 11th after 4 hours of play.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
