<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98122318831071></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98122318831071><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=98122318831071>RE: Bolts</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=98122318831071#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Feb 3rd 6:03 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I did not discover this till lvl 16 and had considered bolts not worth the trouble till then.  That is the main advantage of bolts is that they have a 300 foot range instead of a 200 foot like most spells.  My favorite lvl 16 tactic is to cast sheldskin which absorbs 55? hit points, cast invisible on myself, walk around till i find the perfect target, measure out 300 feet as best i can.  Hit it with a lightnig bolt for 108 damabe, as it runs toward me hit it with flame shock for 102?  If both spells are unresisted the target reaches me with 200+ hitpoints gone, and I have 55 extra hp.  Which you need cuz with each lvl your melee skills fall further and further behind the targets you typically attack.  I have killed a couple of yellows this way, something I haven't done since lvl 3.  Most yellows I end up running from even with a 250+ hp head start, so I only take them on when I'm near someplace safe I can run to.  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
